Daily Need Group, in association with Sparklight Hospital, has inaugurated a clinic facility to serve its members of staff at the company’s premises. The new facility was unveiled by the Chairman of Daily Need Group, Otunba Oyin Jolayemi, who affirmed that the company has the approval of Lagos State Government for the clinic. He expressed his excitement on the success of the project and thanked everyone who had supported it. “This is amazing and I’m really excited about it, we have a number of people working with us and this facility we have at hand will serve them and it is approved by the Lagos State Government,”Jolayemi said.   ‘Access Bank, supporter of women-led businesses’     Nigerian tech start-ups raise $343m in 3 months     Nigeria orders N1.75 trillion wheat as importation soars   Managing Director, Daily-Need Group, Oluwatosin Jolayemi described the event as a dream come true. “It is something we’ve always wanted to have for the benefit of the staff so that they will have access to wellness on our premises before they go out and to be able to give them what I will call a minimal standard of healthcare within our premises even before sending them to any other facility,” Jolayemi said. Medical Director, Sparklight Hospital, Ahmed Omilana was impressed that the company has the love of its staff at heart and appreciated the directors and members of the management for honouring the hospital with the project.   He said that operation has started at the clinic immediately.